body:
The current implementation accumulates a string to be passed to regexp.Compile. Strings in Golang are immutable; therefore, a new string must be allocated for every modification/accumulation.

Prefer a strings.Builder instead, which reduces the amount of allocations and copying.

`strings.Builder` is not goroutine/concurrency-safe, but neither is the existing usage of `text/scanner`.

